SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Objects
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All animate and inanimate entities, both natural and supernatural

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Beings
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All living beings, whether natural or supernatural

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Deities
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All supernatural beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Creatures
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All the natural animate entities, such as humans and animals

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Animals
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This lexical domain consists of all living creatures, with the exception of human beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Wild Animals
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Wild animals of the larger variety. According to the taxonomy that surfaces in the Old Testament (see Lev. 11:29) smaller wild animals, such as the mouse or the weasel, are to be considered |uSmall Animals|u*

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Domestic Animals
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All domesticated animals. Even though this term is occasionally used to indicate animals in a wider sense of the word it usually refers to domestic animals only

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Small Animals
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This category consists of small land animals. According to Genesis 1:24 this is a category in itself. It does somewhat overlap with שֶׁרֶץ, however. Leviticus 11:29 refers to (part of) this subcategory of animals as שֶׁרֶץ הַשֹּׁרֵץ עַל־הָאָרֶץ which refers to all land animals that have short legs (reptiles) or no legs at all (snakes). To use the term reptiles would be incorrect as small mammals, such as the mouse and the weasel, are part of this subcategory as well

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Aquatic Animals
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This category consists of all water creatures except what is considered שֶׁרֶץ הַמַּיִם (see Swarming Creatures). See Leviticus 11:9-12; Deuteronomy 14:9,10

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Birds
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All birds, covered by the Hebrew generic term עוֹף. Flying insects are part of the category Swarming Creatures

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Swarming Creatures
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All animals covered by the generic term שֶׁרֶץ, with the exception of the reptiles and small rodents that are classified as רֶמֶשׂ Small Animals. This comprises what is referred to as שֶׁרֶץ הָעוֹף (Lev. 11:20), שֶׁרֶץ הַמַּיִם (Lev. 11:10), and probably the smaller species of the שֶׁרֶץ הַשֹׂרֵץ עַל־הָאָרֶץ (Lev. 11:29)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: People
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This lexical domain covers all human beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Classes
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Social classes, such as slave, free, alien, rich, poor, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Enemies
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: People that one considers one's enemies, opponents, adversaries, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Friends
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: People that one considers one's friends, companions, partners, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Leaders
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Kings and other leaders

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Officials
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Officials in the service of a king or other leader

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Priests
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Priests and other religious offices

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Professions
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All people engaged in a certain professional activity, such as farmers, craftsmen, fishermen, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Prophets
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Seer and prophets

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Prostitutes
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Adulterers and prostitutes, both male and female

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Relatives
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: People that are related by blood or marriage.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Soldiers
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All people involved in military activities

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Parts
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All objects that cannot exist in isolation but are an integral part of another object and therefore usually occur as part of an associative construction (branch of a tree, wing of a dove, etc.), or require a possessive pronoun (my hand, her head, etc.)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Vegetation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This lexical domain covers all plants and trees

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Plants
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All plants

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Trees
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All trees

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Products
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This lexical domain covers all inanimate objects, usually of a relatively small size, produced by people, deities, animals, or plants. An important characteristic of this category is that this type of objects can be actively used as instruments in other processes. In figures of speech objects of this category often take the place of the events in which they are used as instruments

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Artifacts
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All human-made objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Banners
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All flags, banner, standards and other objects that function as visible signs.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Clothing
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms referring to clothing and armor

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Containers
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All objects produced to contain other objects such as liquids or dry substances

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cords
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Objects such as cords, chains, fetters and similar objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Coverings
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All objects that are used to cover other objects, such as the lid of a jar, the coverings of the tabernacle, or a saddle-cloth to ride on. For clothes, see Clothing

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cult Objects
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All objects that are the object of worship, such as idols, scared pillars, sacred poles,etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Furnishings
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All objects used to furnish and decorate the inside of buildings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Gemstones
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All precious stones

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Jewellery
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All jewellery, such as rings, necklaces, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Scrolls
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Scrolls, tablets, seals, and all other writing equipment

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Ships
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All vehicles used for transportation over water

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Tools
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All artifacts used by craftsmen to produce other artifacts

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Traps
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All instruments used for hunting and fishing, of which פַּח may be a prototype. These objects are often used in a metaphorical sense to denote devices used by evil people to ensnare others

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Vehicles
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All vehicles used for transportation over land

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Weapons
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All artifacts used in warfare

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Body Products
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All body products, such as excrement, sweat, blood, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Food
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms for food items. It must be noted that many food items can be regarded as substances as well. Honey, for instance, is both a food product and a substance. That fact that it is a substance, however, seems to be less relevant than its membership of of the food domain

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Crops
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All crops growing as plants, such as grain, wheat, barley, flax, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dairy
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All food produced by animals, such as dairy products, but also eggs and honey

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Fruits
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All fruits

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Wine
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Wine and related drinks, such as vinegar and liquor

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Scenery
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This lexical domain covers all inanimate objects, with the exception of plants, that usually cannot be moved, and are part of the scenery in which events in the Old Testament take place, like mountains, rivers, population centers, constructions, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Constructions
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All constructions, such as huts, shelters, houses, fortresses, and palaces

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Buildings
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All permanent constructions where people live

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cultic Sites
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All places where religious activities are concentrated, such as shrines, temples, high places, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Fortifications
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All constructions that serve as fortifications

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Stalls
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All constructions where domestic animals are kept

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Tents
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All temporary constructions, such as tents, shelters, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Tombs
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All terms referring to burial places

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Towns
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All population centers, such as villages and towns

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Universe
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Heaven and earth and all that is in it

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Substances
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All inanimate objects that are shaped in such a way that they usually cannot be counted but are to be measured instead, and from which other objects can be produced, e.g. gold, silver, wood, clay, etc. This category includes liquids like water, and elements like fire. These objects are either exclusively used in the singular, or in the shape of a fixed plural or dual form

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cloth
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Cloth and substances used for making clothes, such as פֵּשֶׁת "linen" and צֶמֶר "wool"

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dust
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All small particles covering the earth, such as dust, ashes, soot, sand, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Fire
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Terms such as fire, spark, flame, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Liquids
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All liquids

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Metals
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All metals

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Paint
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Substances used to color other objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Rain
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All forms of precipitation, such as rain, hail, snow

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Spices
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Substances such as fragrant spices, powders, and ointments used for culinary, medicinal, and cosmetic purposes

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Stone
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All types of אֶבֶן; includes rocks, cliffs, etc. for precious stones, see: Gemstones

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Events
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All states, processes, actions, and causative actions, featuring one or more objects or other events. States and Processes overlap in biblical Hebrew and are therefore considered one single category in SDBH (State/Process). Terms that are often labeled abstracts or attributes in semantic theory function as states in biblical Hebrew and are therefore considered events

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Description
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events that describe features of objects or other events. This includes certain adjectives and adverbs, words that according to Nida's analysis usually classify as abstracts rather than events. In biblical Hebrew, however, the distinction between events and abstracts does not work very well, as there is much overlap between the two semantic classes

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Attribute
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the physical features of an object

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Able
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the ability to do certain things.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Alive
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of being alive or not

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Bad
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting good quality

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Burn
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving fire, e.g. בער

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Capacity
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Units of capacity, including both dry and liquid measures

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Clean
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: opposite Unclean

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Close
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of not having an opening allowing entrance, passage, or access, or where that opening has been blocked

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cold
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of having a relatively low temperature

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Color
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of having a particular color, e.g

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cooked
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting that food items have been made ready for human consumption by cooking, boiling, frying, baking, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dead
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of being dead

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Different
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting dissimilarity between objects and events

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dimension
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the dimensions of objects, such as length, width, height, depth, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dry
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the absence of water or moisture

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Impact
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of something being impacted by a certain action. which may be either constructive or destructive.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Ingest
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the process of animate beings taking in food and drink

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Excrete
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the excretion of body products, e.g. spitting, urinating, sweating, vomiting, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Fat
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: opposite: Thin

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Good
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting good quality

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Heavy
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of having a relatively great weight, e.g. כבד

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hot
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of having a relatively high temperature

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: High
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: opposite: Low

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Intact
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of being intact, without damage

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Large
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the relatively small large size of objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Little
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the relatively small size of objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Low
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: opposite: High

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Old
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting relatively old age, e.g. זָקֵן

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Open
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of having an opening allowing entrance, passage, or access

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Poor
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events pertaining to a lack of resources that, according to popular opinion, are required for a life of well-being

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Pregnant
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving conception resulting in pregnancy.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Quantity
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the quantity of objects, e.g. numerals

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Quench
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the putting out of fire

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Raw
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting that food items have not been cooked.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Rich
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events pertaining to the possession of an abundance of resources that, according to popular opinion, are required for a life of well-being

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Shape
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the shape of objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Shine
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the production or reflection of light

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Sick
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of suffering from some sort of sickness

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Similar
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting similarity between objects and events

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Soft
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of being malleable, yielding to pressure

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Solid
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving the attribute of being firm, unyielding to pressure

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Smoke
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events whereby objects produce smoke, usually as a result of fire

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Spasm
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving contractions of the muscles, such as the contractions that accompany the birth of a child

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Stage
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the stage of growth of an object; applies to plants, animals, and human beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Stance
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving stances of the body of humans and animals

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Strong
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting physical strength

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Thin
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: opposite: Fat

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Unable
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the inability to do certain things, as a result of a physical challenge, being overcome by emotions, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Unclean
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: opposite: Clean

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Weak
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the absence of physical strength

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Weight
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: units of weight

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Wet
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the presence of water or moisture

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Young
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting that an object is relatively young

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Attitude
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing non-physical features of (usually animate) objects, such as attitudes and emotions

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Afraid
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting an emotion of fear

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Angry
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting an emotion of anger or displeasure

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Confident
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting an attitude of confidence and lack of fear

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cruel
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing a lack of compassion towards other animate or sometimes even inanimate beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Despise
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting a lack of respect for someone else

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Diligent
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting a willingness to work hard

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Evil
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: רשׁע

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Faithful
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting that someone is committed to stick to one's obligations

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Ferocious
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting an inclination for violence

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Great
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the greatness of people and/or supernatural beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Grieve
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing an emotion of grief or sadness

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hate
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting an attitude of hatred

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Insignificant
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the relative insignificance of certain people and/or supernatural beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Just
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: צדק

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Lazy
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: עָצֵל

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Love
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting an attitude of affection

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Merciful
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the attitude of compassion, e.g. חנן

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Patient
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing an attitude of patience

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Rejoice
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing an emotion of joy or gladness

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Respect
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: כבד

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Shame
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing an emotion of shame or a state of feeling let down by another object, such as a human being or deity

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Willing
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting a willingness to associate or be involved with a person, object, or activity

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Wise
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting people's skill, intelligence, or wisdom

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Unwilling
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing an animate object's refusal to associate or be involved with another object or event.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Modification
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the features of events

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Complicated
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events that take relatively much wisdom or special skills to perform

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Easy
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Something that causes little physical or mental effort

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: False
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events signifying that another event cannot be relied on to be true

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Frequency
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the frequency with which an event occurs

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hard
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events requiring a lot of physical or mental effort

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Intense
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the intensity or force with which other events take place, e.g. חזק

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Lax
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the lack of intensity or force with which other events take place, e.g

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Right
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the extent to which a particular event is morally and/or ethically right

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Simple
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events that take relatively little wisdom or special skills to perform

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: True
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events signifying that another event can be relied on to be true

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Wrong
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the extent to which a particular event is morally and/or ethically wrong

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Position
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relations between objects and events and the environment in which they are located or occur

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Location
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relations between objects and the physical environment in which they are located

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dwell
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: to make one's temporary or permanent abode in a certain location, e.g. שׁכן

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Flee
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (2) to go to another location to save one's life (Action)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hide
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be in a certain location with the purpose not to be seen by certain people (State/Process); (2) to go to a certain location with the purpose not to be seen by certain people (Action), and (3) to put another object certain location for this same pur

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Move
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting movement from one place to another

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Orientation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events and states denoting positions that are relative to other objects, such as front, back, side, north, east, south, west, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Search
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: to try to find out the location of an object, e.g. בקשׁ

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Space
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be in a certain location (State/Process), (2) to take position in a certain location (Action), or (3) to put an object in a certain location (Causative), e.g. עמד

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Non-Space
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to not be in a certain location (State/Process), (2) to disappear from a certain location (Action), or (3) to cause an object to disappear from a certain location (Causative), e.g. אַיִן

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Pursue
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: e.g. רדף

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Existence
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relations between objects and the non-physical environment (existence, time, etc.) in which they are located

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Act
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: This lexical domain contains lexicalized metaphors regarding life as a journey; (2) to behave in a certain way, and (3) to cause to behave in a certain way

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Non-Act
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: to defer action, either permanently or for a certain period

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Birth
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the coming in existence of humans and animals by way of birth; (1) to be born (State/Process), (2) to give birth (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Exist
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the coming in existence of objects by way of |bcreation|b* or |bmanufacturing|b*; (1) to be produced or brought forth (State/Process), (2) to produce or bring forth an object (Action), or (3) to cause an object to be produced or brought

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Non-Exist
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the removal of objects from existence; (1) to be removed from existence (State/Process), (2) to remove oneself from existence (Action), or (3) to remove another object from existence (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Time
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing existence in time rather than in space

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Festivals
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing fixed times for religious festivals and other special occasions

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Occurrence
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relations between other events and the environment in which they occur

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Happen
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to happen (State/Process), (2) to perform an event (Action), or (3) to cause something to happen (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Non-Happen
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to not happen (State/Process), (2) to refrain from performing an event, or (3) to keep something from happen (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Connection
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relations between Objects and Events that are closely associated with one another.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Attachment
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relations of physical attachment between objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Attach
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be attached to another object (State/Process), (2) to attach oneself to another object (Action), or to tie one object to another

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Bind
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be bound (with a rope or in chains) (State/Process), (2) to bind oneself (Action), or (3) to bind someone or something else (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Carry
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to carry an object (State/Process), (2) to pick up an object (Action), or (3) to cause someone else to carry an object

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cover
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be covered by something (State/Process), (2) to cover oneself (Action), and (3) to cover something else (Causative); for covering oneself with clothes or armor, see: Dress

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dress
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to wear clothes or armor (State/Process), (2) to put on clothes or armor (Action), or (3) or to dress or arm someone else

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Detach
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be detached from another object (State/Process), (2) to detach oneself from another object (Action), or (3) to detach one object from another

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hang
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events relating to objects being attached to other objects from above, with the lower part not attached

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hold
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to hold an object in one's hand (State/Process), (2) to take hold of an object with one's hand (Action), or (3) to cause someone else to hold an object in his/her hand (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Pure
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing that objects are homogenous and free from other ingredients

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Undress
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be naked (State/Process), (2) to take of one's clothes (Action), or (3) to strip someone else (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Uncover
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to becone uncovered (State/Process), (2) to uncover oneself (Action), and (3) to uncover something else (Causative); for taking off one's clothes or armor, see: |uStrip|u*

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Unite
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Divide

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Association
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relationships of non-physical attachment between objects (e.g. possession, acquaintance)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Worship
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting people showing reverence and adoration for a deity

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Apart
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be apart from other, related objects (State/Process), (2) to separate oneself from other, related objects (Action), and (3) to set an object apart from other, related objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Associate
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be in league with an individual or group for a common purpose (State/Process), (2) to join oneself to an individual or group for a common purpose, and (3) to bring to individuals or groups together for a common purpose

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Conflict
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: to be engaged in a conflict with another individual or group, which does no go beyond a verbal argument but may escalate into a physical fight or even warfare

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Control
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to have control over someone else (State/Process), (2) to put oneself in control of someone else (Action), and (3) to put someone else in control of someone (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Dissociate
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting that an individual or group is denied access to a certain community or country, either temporarily or permanently

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Forsake
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to disassociate oneself from something (Action)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Gather
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events involving both animate and inanimate objects being brought together in one location, e.g. (1) to be gathered together in one place (State/Process), (2) to come together (Action), or (3) to bring together (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Help
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be a helper to someone or to support someone (State/Process), (2) to help someone (Action), or (3) to cause someone to help someone else

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Meet
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing objects that meet each other while moving from one place to another; (1) to meet another object (unintentionally, State/Process), (2) to go to meet another object (intentionally, Action), and (3) to cause two objects to meet each other (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Non-Possess
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be not in possession or lose possession of an object (State/Process); (2) to dispose of an object that one possesses (Action); (3) to cause someone else to lose possession of an object (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Possess
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be in possession or gain possession of an object (State/Process); (2) to take possession of an object (Action); (3) to give someone else possession of an object (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Sacrifice
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (2) to present an offering to a deity (Action)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Scatter
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be scattered (State/Process), (2) to scatter (oneselves), and (3) to cause other people to scatter (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Serve
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing humans serving deities or other humans

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Involvement
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relationships between objects and events (e.g. involvement, commitment)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Attain
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to be in or attain a certain state or position (State/Process), (2) to procure a certain state of position for oneself (Action), and (3) to grant a certain state or position to someone else (Causative)
SemanticDomainLocalization.Comment: Some of the events of this category can be considered lexicalized metaphors featuring events of the category |uPossess|u*, where one of the objects in the semantic argument structure has been replaced by an event

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Affect
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to affect someone (of events; State/Process), and (3) to cause an event to affect someone else (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Bear
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to bear the responsibility an event (State/Process), (2) to take the responsibility for an event upon oneself (Action), or (3) to put the responsibility of an event upon someone else (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Continue
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting the continuation of another event that has started earlier.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Guilty
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting that people are responsible for a particular action.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Innocent
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting that people are not responsible for a particular action.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Sin
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to live in a state of guilt (State/Process), (2) to be involved in morally or ethically unjust activities (Action), or (3) to lead other people astray (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Safe
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting a situation in which one is free from hardship; (1) to be free from hardship (State/Process); (2) to protect or save oneself from hardship (Action), or (3) to protect or save someone else from hardship

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Try
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting someone's effort to perform another event

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Unsafe
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting hardship

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Perception
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing relations between objects and events and the mind of animate beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Sensation
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the physical aspects of the relationship between objects and events and the mind of animate beings (e.g. seeing, hearing, smelling, feeling, etc.)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Feel
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the physical aspects of the relationship

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Desire
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to experience a physical desire

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hunger
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to feel hungry (State/Process)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Thirst
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to feel thirst (State/Process); prototype: צמ

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Touch
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to feel (State/Process), (2) to touch (Action), (3) to cause to feel (Causative), משׁש

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Hear
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to hear (State/Process), (2) to listen (Action), or (3) to cause to hear (Causative), e.g. |bשׁמע|b*

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: See
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to see (State/Process), (2) to look (Action), or (3) to cause to see, show (Causative), e.g. ראה

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Smell
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to smell (State/Process), (2) to sniff (Action), (3) to cause to smell (Causative), e.g. באשׁ

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Taste
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to taste (while eating or drinking = State/Process), (2) to taste (on purpose = Action), or (3) to cause to taste (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Utter
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: to utter sounds

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Ask
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing utterances involving a request, usually part of a conversation between humans. For requests adressed to a deity, see |uPray|u*.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Complain
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: e.g. לו

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Speak
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to speak (Action), or (2) to cause to speak (Causative)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Praise
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Mock

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Pray
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting people addressing prayers to a deity

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cognition
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the non-physical aspects of the relationship between objects and events and the mind of animate beings (e.g. knowing, thinking, remembering, etc.)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Sense
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing inner feelings of people

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Wish
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: (1) to long for something to happen (State/Process

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Cause
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: to be the cause or reason for something to happen

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Judge
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: To make a decision concerning an individual or group, usually to determine whether their actions are right or wrong

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Know
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events dealing with information stored in the brain; (1) to know, learn, remember (State/Process); (2) to study (Action); (3) to teach (Causative), e.g. ידע; opposite Forget

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Partial
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events denoting people giving preferential treatment to some to the exclusion of others.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Think
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Events describing the processing of information by the brain; (2) to think (Action)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Referents
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All lexical units that substitute for objects and events

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Object Referents
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All lexical units that substitute for objects

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of Constructions
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of constructions, such as towers, gates, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of Groups
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of ethnic groups, communities, etc

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of People
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of individuals

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of Landforms
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of landforms, such as mountains, valleys, rocks, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of Languages
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of languages

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of Locations
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of towns, villages, areas, and other population centers

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of Supernatural Beings
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of deities and other supernatural beings

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of Times
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of periods of time, especially months

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Names of Waterbodies
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All names of bodies of water, such as seas, rivers, streams, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Titles
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: All titles and other ways to address people and deities while not using their names

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Markers
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Relationals that are used to highlight or put the focus on a particular object or event, e.g. הִנֵּה (GEN.12:19), אַךְ (GEN.7:23), גַּם (GEN.3:6)

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Affirmers
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Markers pointing to the probability of a particular statement

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Contrastors
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Markers pointing to new information that is an unexpected consequence of what has been stated previously

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Identifiers
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Relationals that put the focus on a particular object or event, e.g. הִנֵּה see, including definite articles and demonstratives

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Extenders
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Relationals indicating that than object or event has been added to the range of objects/events in focus, e.g. גַּם also

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Evaluators
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Marker expressing an opinion concerning the information that it introduces, which may be one of joy, regret, etc.

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Negators
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Relationals that negate an event, e.g. לֹא

SemanticDomainLocalization.Label: Restrictors
SemanticDomainLocalization.Description: Relationals indicating that an object or event is the only object/event in focus, e.g. אַךְ
